codex
The reject test was failing before reaching the chi-square gate because its default estimator state placed the receiver at Earth’s center; it now seeds a valid receiver state and verifies the update count is unchanged. The e2e test’s near-zero correction was caused by an epsilon-variance GNSS setup collapsing all velocity covariance, so I’ve retained bounded geometry while leaving enough covariance for the deliberate 0.5 m/s innovation to produce an observable, bounded correction.
